    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "\n### Feature description\n\nRight now in the latest code, looks like the cmake scripts in `cmake.deps` directory use the default cmake download (or built-in `curl`) which generally isn't build with `SSL` support by default. This fails to work for `https` urls like `Github`.\n\nCan we add an option to let developers to use customized command such as `wget` or system's `curl` to download the dependencies in `ExternalProject_Add()`?\n\nFor example, we can add a customized `DOWNLOAD_COMMAND` that developer provides in `ExternalProject_Add`? Thanks",
