            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> We are in a controlled (i.e., non-root user) env where the default cmake is actually not built with SSL support\n\nI recently had a similar use-case. The `USE_EXISTING_SRC_DIR` approach works, though somewhat clumsy. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36610 improves the docs for it (\"offline builds\").\n\nNote: https://github.com/neovim/deps/tree/master/src is an auto-updated snapshot of the `.deps/build/src/` needed to build offline with `USE_EXISTING_SRC_DIR`.\n\n> Are you not able to manually build cmake with SSL-support?\n\nIn some cases, no. And the build environment may not have network access.",
